; Regression test for issue #698: When format_t outputs a balance, it should know the next line width (BZ#698)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/698
;
; When a format string uses justify() on a multi-commodity balance followed by
; other content (like %(account)), the account name should appear on the first
; line and subsequent balance lines should be padded to the same width.
; Currently, the account name appears on the last line and intermediate lines
; are not padded - demonstrating that format_t does not know the next line width.

2024/01/01 Test multi-commodity
    Assets:Stocks   10 AAPL @ $150.00
    Assets:Bonds    5 BOND @ $100.00
    Assets:Cash     -$2000.00

test bal --format '%(justify(scrub(display_total), 20)) %(account)\n'
$-2000.00           
10 AAPL
5 BOND Assets
5 BOND               Assets:Bonds
$-2000.00            Assets:Cash
10 AAPL              Assets:Stocks
$-2000.00           
10 AAPL
5 BOND 
end test
